               "# Python style guide\n\n## General\n\n- Use Poetry and `pyproject.toml`; add console scripts for CLIs.\n- typing: `from __future__ import annotations`, `mypy` clean where feasible.\n- Structure: src/ layout, no implicit namespace pkgs.\n- Tests: `pytest -q`; prefer small, focused unit tests\n\n## Functional Python\n\n- Always generate functional python when possible\n- Always separate data out into pure data classes\n- Use pure functions and follow Stratified Design and Simple Made Easy principles.",
